        last_assistant_message: "Now let me create a comprehensive summary document with everything I've learned:\n\n## COMPREHENSIVE STATE SUMMARY: Orchestra MCP Packs System & Distribution\n\nBased on a thorough read of all implementation files, here's the complete current state:\n\n### **1. PACKS SYSTEM — FULLY BUILT**\n\n#### **A. Pack Index (libs/plugin-tools-marketplace/internal/packs/index.go)**\n- **17 known packs** defined statically in `KnownPacks`\n- Packs organized by technology stack: go, rust, react, typescript, docker, swift, kotlin, csharp, c, etc.\n- Each pack has:\n  - `Repo`: GitHub URL (e.g., `github.com/orchestra-mcp/pack-go-backend`)\n  - `Stacks`: Array of applicable stacks (supports wildcard `*`)\n  - `Description`: Human-readable text\n  - `Tags`: Search keywords\n\n**Functions:**\n- `RecommendPacks(stacks []string)` → filters packs by detected/configured stacks\n- `SearchPacks(query string)` → full-text search across repo, description, tags, stacks\n\n**Known Packs (17):**\n1. pack-essentials (all stacks)\n2. pack-go-backend (go)\n3. pack-rust-engine (rust)\n4. pack-react-frontend (react, typescript)\n5. pack-database (all stacks)\n6. pack-ai (all stacks)\n7. pack-mobile (react-native)\n8. pack-desktop (go)\n9. pack-extensions (all stacks)\n10. pack-chrome (typescript)\n11. pack-infra (docker)\n12. pack-proto (go, rust)\n13. pack-native-swift (swift)\n14. pack-native-kotlin (kotlin, java)\n15. pack-native-csharp (csharp)\n16. pack-native-gtk (c)\n17. pack-analytics (all stacks)\n\n#### **B. Pack Installation (libs/plugin-tools-marketplace/internal/packs/installer.go)**\n- **Type:** `PackManifest` parsed from `pack.json` in pack repos\n- **Installation Flow:**\n  1. Git clone pack repo to temp directory (shallow, depth=1)\n  2. Parse `pack.json` (name, version, description, stacks, contents)\n  3. Copy skills from `<tmpDir>/skills/*` to `<workspace>/.claude/skills/<name>/`\n  4. Copy agents from `<tmpDir>/agents/*.md` to `<workspace>/.claude/agents/`\n  5. Copy hooks from `<tmpDir>/hooks/*.sh` to `<workspace>/.claude/hooks/`\n  6. Delete temp directory\n\n**Functions:**\n- `InstallPack(workspace, repo, version)` → installs pack, returns manifest\n- `RemovePack(workspace, skills, agents, hooks)` → removes installed files\n- `ListInstalledSkills(workspace)` → scans `.claude/skills/`, returns names\n- `ListInstalledAgents(workspace)` → scans `.claude/agents/`, returns names\n- `ListInstalledHooks(workspace)` → scans `.claude/hooks/`, returns names\n- `ReadSkillContent(workspace, name)` → reads `.claude/skills/<name>/SKILL.md`\n- `ReadAgentContent(workspace, name)` → reads `.claude/agents/<name>.md`\n\n**Storage:** Packs stored in workspace at `.claude/skills/`, `.claude/agents/`, `.claude/hooks/`\n\n#### **C. Stack Detection (libs/plugin-tools-marketplace/internal/packs/stacks.go)**\n- **Type:** `StackInfo` with name, confidence, evidence\n- **Detection Checks (12 stacks):**\n  - Go: `go.mod`, `go.work`\n  - Rust: `Cargo.toml`\n  - React: `react` in `package.json` dependencies\n  - TypeScript: `tsconfig.json`\n  - Python: `pyproject.toml`, `requirements.txt`, `setup.py`\n  - Ruby: `Gemfile`\n  - Java: `pom.xml`, `build.gradle`\n  - Kotlin: `build.gradle.kts`\n  - Swift: `Package.swift` or `*.xcodeproj`\n  - C#: `*.csproj` or `*.sln`\n  - PHP: `composer.json`\n  - Docker: `Dockerfile`, `docker-compose.yml`, `docker-compose.yaml`\n\n**Function:** `DetectStacks(workspace)` → returns array of StackInfo\n\n#### **D. Tools (6 pack-management tools)**\nFile: `libs/plugin-tools-marketplace/internal/tools/pack.go`\n\n**Tools:**\n1. `install_pack(repo, version?)` → installs pack, updates registry\n2. `remove_pack(name)` → removes pack, updates registry\n3. `update_pack(name?)` → updates one or all packs\n4. `list_packs(type?)` → lists installed packs, optional filter (skills/agents/hooks)\n5. `get_pack(name)` → shows details of installed pack\n6. `search_packs(query, stack?)` → searches available packs\n\n**Storage:** Registry at `.packs/registry.json` via marketplace storage client\n\n#### **E. Prompts (5 prompts)**\nFile: `libs/plugin-tools-marketplace/internal/tools/prompts.go`\n\n**Prompts:**\n1. `setup-project` → detect stacks, show recommended packs\n2. `recommend-packs` → show packs for detected/configured stacks\n3. `audit-packs` → show installed packs summary\n4. `search-marketplace` → search and display available packs\n5. `onboard-project` → full workflow (create → detect → install → verify)\n\n#### **F. Content Tools (5 content query tools)**\nFile: `libs/plugin-tools-marketplace/internal/tools/content.go`\n\n**Tools:**\n1. `list_skills()` → lists installed skills\n2. `list_agents()` → lists installed agents\n3. `list_hooks()` → lists installed hooks\n4. `get_skill(name)` → reads skill's SKILL.md\n5. `get_agent(name)` → reads agent's markdown\n\n#### **G. Configuration Tools (2 config tools)**\nFile: `libs/plugin-tools-marketplace/internal/tools/config.go`\n\n**Tools:**\n1. `set_project_stacks(stacks[])` → saves manually configured stacks\n2. `get_project_stacks()` → returns configured stacks or auto-detected\n\n**Storage:** Stacks at `.packs/stacks.json` via storage client\n\n#### **H. Plugin Registration (libs/plugin-tools-marketplace/internal/plugin.go)**\n- `MarketplacePlugin` struct with `Storage` (PackStorage) and `Workspace`\n- Registers **15 tools** (6 pack-management + 2 recommendations + 5 content + 2 config)\n- Registers **5 prompts** (setup, recommend, audit, search, onboard)\n- Storage client uses orchestrator's QUIC connection\n\n#### **I. Storage Layer (libs/plugin-tools-marketplace/internal/storage/client.go)**\n- **PackRegistry:** map of pack name → `PackEntry`\n- **PackEntry:** version, repo, installed_at, stacks, skills, agents, hooks\n- **Storage paths:** `.packs/registry.json`, `.packs/stacks.json`\n- **Storage type:** markdown (via orchestrator's storage.markdown plugin)\n- **Read/Write:** Low-level `storageRead()` and `storageWrite()` send protobuf messages to orchestrator\n\n#### **J. Entry Point (libs/plugin-tools-marketplace/cmd/main.go)**\n- Plugin builder: `tools.marketplace` v0.1.0\n- Flag: `--workspace` (default `.`)\n- Adapts orchestrator client to storage.StorageClient interface\n- Runs in stdio server mode\n\n---\n\n### **2. CLI PACKS MANAGEMENT — FULLY BUILT**\n\nFile: `libs/cli/internal/pack.go`\n\n#### **CLI Pack Commands:**\n```\norchestra pack install <repo>[@version]   # Install pack\norchestra pack remove <name>              # Remove pack\norchestra pack update [name]              # Update packs\norchestra pack list                       # List installed packs\norchestra pack search <query>             # Search available packs\norchestra pack recommend                  # Detect stacks & recommend\n```\n\n**Implementation:**\n- Duplicates KnownPacks index from plugin (17 packs)\n- Local registry at `.projects/.packs/registry.json` (different from tool!)\n- Same git clone + file copy logic as plugin\n- Supports `--workspace` flag\n\n**Key Difference:** CLI stores registry in `.projects/.packs/` while tools plugin stores in `.packs/`\n\n---\n\n### **3. PACK REPOSITORIES (18 REPOS)**\n\nLocation: `packs/` directory (full local clones)\n\n**Structure** (example pack-essentials):\n```\npack-essentials/\n├── pack.json           # Manifest: name, version, stacks, contents\n├── README.md\n├── CHANGELOG.md\n├── skills/\n│   ├── project-manager/\n│   ├── qa-testing/\n│   ├── docs/\n│   └── plugin-generator/\n├── agents/\n│   ├── scrum-master.md\n│   ├── devops.md\n│   └── qa-playwright.md\n└── hooks/\n    └── orchestra-mcp-hook.sh\n```\n\n**Pack Manifest (pack.json):**\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"orchestra-mcp/pack-essentials\",\n  \"description\": \"...\",\n  \"version\": \"0.1.0\",\n  \"type\": \"pack\",\n  \"license\": \"MIT\",\n  \"stacks\": [\"*\"],\n  \"contents\": {\n    \"skills\": [\"...\"],\n    \"agents\": [\"...\"],\n    \"hooks\": [\"...\"]\n  },\n  \"tags\": [\"...\"]\n}\n```\n\n**18 Packs Available:**\n- pack-essentials, pack-go-backend, pack-rust-engine, pack-react-frontend\n- pack-database, pack-ai, pack-mobile, pack-desktop, pack-extensions\n- pack-chrome, pack-infra, pack-proto\n- pack-native-swift, pack-native-kotlin, pack-native-csharp, pack-native-gtk\n- pack-analytics\n\n---\n\n### **4. DISTRIBUTION & DEPLOYMENT**\n\n#### **A. Makefile (orchestration)**\nFile: `Makefile`\n\n**Targets:**\n- `build` → builds all 6 binaries (orchestrator, 5 plugins)\n- `build-tools-marketplace` → builds plugin binary to `bin/tools-marketplace`\n- `build-cli` → builds CLI to `bin/orchestra` (with version ldflags)\n- `test-unit` → runs tests across all libs\n- `install` → copies binaries to `/usr/local/bin/`\n- `release` → cross-compiles (darwin/linux × amd64/arm64), creates tarballs in `dist/`\n\n**Binaries Built:**\n1. `bin/orchestrator` — plugin host\n2. `bin/storage-markdown` — storage plugin\n3. `bin/tools-features` — tools plugin\n4. `bin/transport-stdio` — transport plugin\n5. `bin/tools-marketplace` — marketplace plugin\n6. `bin/orchestra` — CLI with version injection\n\n#### **B. GitHub Actions (CI/CD)**\n\n**release.yml (on tag v*):**\n- Builds for 4 platforms (darwin-amd64, darwin-arm64, linux-amd64, linux-arm64)\n- Clones dependencies from `orchestra.lock` (Python script)\n- Builds all 6 binaries per platform\n- Creates tarballs: `orchestra-{os}-{arch}.tar.gz`\n- Creates GitHub Release with artifacts\n\n**ci.yml (on push/PR to master/main):**\n- Installs dependencies from `orchestra.lock`\n- Runs `make build`\n- Runs `make test-unit`\n- Runs `make test-e2e`\n- Lints with `go vet`\n\n#### **C. Homebrew Distribution**\n\nFile: `packaging/homebrew/orchestra.rb`\n\n**Formula:**\n- Installs 6 binaries from GitHub releases: orchestra, orchestrator, storage-markdown, tools-features, transport-stdio, tools-marketplace\n- URLs: `https://github.com/orchestra-mcp/framework/releases/download/v{version}/orchestra-{os}-{arch}.tar.gz`\n- Requires placeholders to be filled: VERSION_PLACEHOLDER, SHA256_DARWIN_ARM64, etc.\n\n**Usage:**\n```bash\nbrew tap orchestra-mcp/tap\nbrew install orchestra\n```\n\n#### **D. Dependency Management**\n\nFile: `orchestra.lock` (JSON)\n\n**Purpose:** Pins exact versions/branches of all dependencies\n\n**Format:**\n```json\n{\n  \"packages\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"...\",\n      \"type\": \"...\",\n      \"path\": \"...\",\n      \"version\": \"...\",\n      \"source\": {\n        \"url\": \"https://github.com/...\",\n        \"reference\": \"master\"\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n**Install Order** (from orchestra.json):\n1. proto\n2. gen-go\n3. sdk-go\n4. orchestrator\n5. plugin-storage-markdown\n6. plugin-tools-features\n7. plugin-transport-stdio\n8. plugin-tools-marketplace\n9. cli\n\n---\n\n### **5. WHAT'S BUILT vs. WHAT NEEDS BUILDING**\n\n#### **✅ FULLY BUILT:**\n\n**Packs System:**\n- Pack index (17 packs defined)\n- Pack installer (git clone + file copy)\n- Stack detection (12 stacks)\n- Registry storage (JSON in `.packs/` or `.projects/.packs/`)\n- 15 MCP tools (install, remove, update, list, search, get, detect_stacks, recommend, list_skills, list_agents, list_hooks, get_skill, get_agent, set_project_stacks, get_project_stacks)\n- 5 prompts (setup, recommend, audit, search, onboard)\n- CLI pack management (`orchestra pack install/remove/update/list/search/recommend`)\n- 18 pack repositories (full local clones with pack.json + skills/agents/hooks)\n\n**Distribution:**\n- Build system (Makefile with cross-compilation)\n- CI/CD (GitHub Actions for build, test, lint, release)\n- Homebrew formula template\n- Dependency locking (orchestra.lock)\n- Version injection in CLI binary\n\n#### **❓ QUESTIONS / POTENTIAL GAPS:**\n\n1. **Packs Distribution:**\n   - Are packs automatically pushed to GitHub repos as separate org repos? (YES — 18 local clones exist but unclear if they sync back)\n   - Who creates/maintains the pack repos? (Appears to be for demonstration, not auto-created)\n\n2. **Registry Sync:**\n   - CLI stores registry at `.projects/.packs/registry.json`\n   - Plugin stores at `.packs/registry.json`\n   - These might diverge — need clarification on sync strategy\n\n3. **Pack Marketplace Hosting:**\n   - Packs are installed from GitHub directly (git clone)\n   - No centralized marketplace API or search service\n   - Packs are defined statically in code (17 hardcoded in both CLI and plugin)\n\n4. **Dependency Resolution:**\n   - Packs don't declare dependencies on other packs\n   - No validation that pack stacks match project stacks beyond recommendation\n   - No conflict detection if multiple packs provide same skill\n\n5. **Marketplace Extensibility:**\n   - How do new packs get discovered? (Manual addition to KnownPacks + orchestra.lock)\n   - Is there a process for community pack submission?\n\n#### **\U0001F528 BUILD STATUS:**\n\n- **Tools Plugin:** Buildable → `go build -o bin/tools-marketplace ./libs/plugin-tools-marketplace/cmd/`\n- **CLI:** Buildable → `go build -o bin/orchestra ./libs/cli/`\n- **Tests:** 66+ unit tests pass (packs/index, packs/stacks, storage, tools)\n- **Release:** Automated via GitHub Actions on git tag\n\n---\n\n### **6. KEY FILES SUMMARY TABLE**\n\n| File | Lines | Purpose |\n|------|-------|---------|\n| `libs/plugin-tools-marketplace/internal/packs/index.go` | 86 | Pack index (17 packs) + search |\n| `libs/plugin-tools-marketplace/internal/packs/installer.go` | 222 | Git clone + install logic |\n| `libs/plugin-tools-marketplace/internal/packs/stacks.go` | 119 | Stack detection (12 stacks) |\n| `libs/plugin-tools-marketplace/internal/tools/pack.go` | 359 | 6 pack-management tools |\n| `libs/plugin-tools-marketplace/internal/tools/prompts.go` | 353 | 5 prompts |\n| `libs/plugin-tools-marketplace/internal/tools/content.go` | 152 | 5 content query tools |\n| `libs/plugin-tools-marketplace/internal/tools/config.go` | 85 | 2 config tools |\n| `libs/plugin-tools-marketplace/internal/storage/client.go` | 171 | Storage client (registry + stacks) |\n| `libs/plugin-tools-marketplace/internal/plugin.go` | 95 | Plugin registration (15 tools + 5 prompts) |\n| `libs/plugin-tools-marketplace/cmd/main.go` | 78 | Plugin entry point |\n| `libs/plugin-tools-marketplace/internal/packs/packs_test.go` | 329 | 20+ unit tests |\n| `libs/cli/internal/pack.go` | 525 | CLI pack commands (duplicated logic) |\n| `libs/cli/internal/registry.go` | 76 | Plugin registry (separate from packs) |\n| `libs/cli/main.go` | 80 | CLI entry point (10 subcommands) |\n| `.github/workflows/release.yml` | 145 | Release automation (4 platforms) |\n| `.github/workflows/ci.yml` | 91 | CI (build, test, lint) |\n| `Makefile` | 112 | Build orchestration |\n| `orchestra.json` | 47 | Project metadata + dependencies |\n| `orchestra.lock` | Variable | Dependency lock file |\n| `packaging/homebrew/orchestra.rb` | 56 | Homebrew formula template |\n| `packs/pack-*/*.json` | — | 18 pack manifests |\n\n---\n\n### **7. EXECUTION FLOW**\n\n```\nUser: orchestra pack install github.com/orchestra-mcp/pack-go-backend\n\nCLI (libs/cli/internal/pack.go):\n  1. Parse repo + version\n  2. Git clone to temp dir\n  3. Parse pack.json\n  4. Copy skills → .claude/skills/<name>/\n  5. Copy agents → .claude/agents/\n  6. Copy hooks → .claude/hooks/\n  7. Update .projects/.packs/registry.json\n  8. Output summary\n\nMCP Client → orchestra serve:\n  1. Call install_pack(repo, version)\n  \nOrchestrator:\n  1. Routes to tools.marketplace plugin\n  \nPlugin (libs/plugin-tools-marketplace):\n  1. Handler: InstallPack()\n  2. Calls packs.InstallPack() (same logic as CLI)\n  3. Calls ps.ReadRegistry() → storage.markdown\n  4. Calls ps.WriteRegistry() → storage.markdown\n  5. Returns Markdown result\n\nStorage (tools-marketplace client):\n  1. Sends StorageReadRequest(.packs/registry.json)\n  2. Receives StorageReadResponse with metadata\n  3. Parses JSON → PackRegistry\n  4. Updates registry\n  5. Sends StorageWriteRequest(.packs/registry.json)\n```\n\n---\n\n### **CONCLUSION**\n\nThe packs system is **architecturally complete** with:\n- Full implementation of 17-pack index\n- Working installer with git clone + filesystem copy\n- Stack detection for 12 technologies\n- 15 MCP tools covering install/remove/update/search/recommend/content management\n- Parallel CLI implementation with duplicate logic\n- Complete build system and CI/CD automation\n- Homebrew distribution template\n\n**Main gaps:** Centralized marketplace discovery, pack dependency resolution, community submission process. Packs are currently hardcoded and distributed via GitHub repositories with no auto-discovery mechanism beyond the static index."
