    - event_type: PostToolUse
      session_id: 42e039ef-ffda-42b3-aff0-9f3b4aec2a0e
      tool_name: Task
      data:
        cwd: /Users/fadymondy/Sites/orchestra-agents
        hook_event_name: PostToolUse
        permission_mode: acceptEdits
        session_id: 42e039ef-ffda-42b3-aff0-9f3b4aec2a0e
        tool_input:
            description: Explore packs current state
            prompt: |-
                Thoroughly explore the packs system in this repo. I need to understand:

                1. What pack repos exist in packs/ directory? List all of them with their pack.json contents.
                2. What does libs/plugin-tools-marketplace/internal/packs/index.go look like? (the pack definitions)
                3. What does libs/plugin-tools-marketplace/internal/packs/installer.go look like? (the installer)
                4. What does libs/plugin-tools-marketplace/internal/tools/prompts.go look like? (the prompt handlers)
                5. What does libs/cli/internal/pack.go look like? (CLI pack commands)
                6. Does scripts/install.sh exist? If so, what's in it?
                7. Does packaging/homebrew/ exist? What's in it?
                8. Does any npm wrapper exist?
                9. What's in libs/plugin-tools-marketplace/internal/storage/client.go?

                Be very thorough — read full file contents.
            subagent_type: Explore
        tool_name: Task
        tool_response:
            agentId: a818c324438b518c4
            content:
                - text: "Excellent! Now I have all the information I need. Let me create a comprehensive summary of my findings:\n\n## Comprehensive Packs System Exploration Report\n\nI've thoroughly explored the packs system across the repository. Here's what I found:\n\n---\n\n## 1. PACK REPOSITORIES IN `/packs/` DIRECTORY\n\nThere are **17 packs** in total, all with accompanying `pack.json` files:\n\n### Core & Cross-Stack\n- **pack-essentials** — Core project management skills (project-manager, qa-testing, docs, plugin-generator) + agents (scrum-master, devops, qa-playwright) + 1 hook\n- **pack-database** — Database skills (database-sync) + agents (dba, postgres-dba, sqlite-engineer, redis-engineer)\n- **pack-ai** — AI/LLM skills + agents (ai-engineer, lancedb-engineer)\n- **pack-extensions** — Extension system skills + extension-architect agent\n- **pack-infra** — DevOps/Infrastructure skills (gcp-infrastructure) + devops agent\n- **pack-analytics** — ClickHouse analytics + clickhouse-engineer agent\n\n### Language-Specific Backend\n- **pack-go-backend** — Go skills (go-backend) + agents (go-architect, qa-go)\n- **pack-rust-engine** — Rust skills (rust-engine) + agents (rust-engineer, qa-rust)\n- **pack-proto** — Protobuf/gRPC skills (proto-grpc) + quic-protocol agent\n\n### Frontend & UI\n- **pack-react-frontend** — React skills (typescript-react, ui-design, tailwindcss-development) + agents (frontend-dev, ui-ux-designer, qa-node)\n- **pack-chrome** — Chrome extension skills (chrome-extension)\n\n### Platform-Specific\n- **pack-desktop** — Desktop skills (wails-desktop, macos-integration, native-widgets) + agents (platform-engineer, widget-engineer)\n- **pack-mobile** — React Native skills (react-native-mobile) + mobile-dev agent\n- **pack-native-swift** — Swift/macOS/iOS agent (swift-plugin)\n- **pack-native-kotlin** — Kotlin/Android agent (kotlin-plugin)\n- **pack-native-csharp** — C#/Windows agent (csharp-plugin)\n- **pack-native-gtk** — GTK4/Linux agent (gtk-plugin)\n\n### Summary Statistics (from packs/README.md)\n- **22 skills** across 12 packs\n- **26 agents** across 17 packs (devops appears in both essentials and infra)\n- **1 hook** in pack-essentials\n\n---\n\n## 2. PACK MANIFEST FORMAT\n\nEach pack has a `pack.json` file with this structure:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"orchestra-mcp/pack-<name>\",\n  \"description\": \"...\",\n  \"version\": \"0.1.0\",\n  \"type\": \"pack\",\n  \"license\": \"MIT\",\n  \"stacks\": [\"*\"] or [\"go\", \"rust\", ...],\n  \"contents\": {\n    \"skills\": [\"skill-name\", ...],\n    \"agents\": [\"agent-name\", ...],\n    \"hooks\": [\"hook-name\", ...]\n  },\n  \"tags\": [\"tag1\", \"tag2\", ...]\n}\n```\n\n**Pack Directory Structure:**\n```\npack-name/\n├── pack.json          # Required manifest\n├── README.md          # Pack documentation\n├── .gitignore\n├── skills/\n│   └── skill-name/\n│       └── SKILL.md   # Skill definition\n├── agents/\n│   └── agent-name.md  # Agent definition\n└── hooks/\n    └── hook-name.sh   # Hook script\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. PACK DEFINITIONS: `/libs/plugin-tools-marketplace/internal/packs/index.go`\n\nThis file contains the **built-in registry** of known packs. It includes:\n\n- **PackInfo struct**: Repo, Stacks (array), Description, Tags\n- **KnownPacks variable**: Array of 17 hardcoded PackInfo entries matching all repos in `/packs/`\n\n**Key Functions:**\n- `RecommendPacks(stacks []string)` → Filters packs matching given stacks (handles \"*\" wildcard)\n- `SearchPacks(query string)` → Full-text search across repo names, descriptions, and tags\n- `matchesPack(p PackInfo, query string)` → Helper for case-insensitive substring matching\n\nAll 17 packs are enumerated here with their exact repo paths, stacks, descriptions, and tags for discovery.\n\n---\n\n## 4. PACK INSTALLER: `/libs/plugin-tools-marketplace/internal/packs/installer.go`\n\n**Core Data Structures:**\n- `PackManifest` — Parsed pack.json with Name, Description, Version, Type, License, Stacks, Contents (Skills/Agents/Hooks), Tags\n- `RemovePack()` — Uninstalls and deletes files\n- `ListInstalledSkills/Agents/Hooks()` — Scans `.claude/skills/`, `.claude/agents/`, `.claude/hooks/`\n- `ReadSkillContent()` — Reads `.claude/skills/<name>/SKILL.md`\n- `ReadAgentContent()` — Reads `.claude/agents/<name>.md`\n\n**InstallPack(workspace, repo, version) Flow:**\n1. Validates git is available\n2. Creates temp directory\n3. Git clones repo with optional `--branch <version>` (shallow clone: `--depth 1`)\n4. Reads and parses `pack.json` from temp\n5. Copies:\n   - Skills: `tmpDir/skills/<name>` → `.claude/skills/<name>/` (recursive)\n   - Agents: `tmpDir/agents/<name>.md` → `.claude/agents/<name>.md`\n   - Hooks: `tmpDir/hooks/<name>.sh` → `.claude/hooks/<name>.sh` (chmod 0755)\n6. Returns the parsed manifest or error\n\n**Helper Functions:**\n- `copyDir()` / `copyFile()` — Recursive directory and single-file copying\n- No external dependencies — purely filesystem operations\n\n---\n\n## 5. PROMPT HANDLERS: `/libs/plugin-tools-marketplace/internal/tools/prompts.go`\n\n**5 Prompts Registered:**\n\n### A. `setup-project` \n**Args:** `project_name` (required)\n**Flow:** \n- Auto-detect stacks\n- Get recommended packs\n- Check installed packs (from storage)\n- Output Markdown with detected stacks, recommended packs, install instructions\n\n### B. `recommend-packs`\n**Args:** `stacks` (optional, comma-separated)\n**Flow:**\n- Use provided stacks OR read configured stacks OR auto-detect\n- Call `RecommendPacks(stackNames)`\n- Load installed packs registry\n- Output Markdown with recommendations and installation status\n\n### C. `audit-packs`\n**Args:** None\n**Flow:**\n- Load registry from storage\n- If empty: suggest `recommend_packs` or `search_packs`\n- If packs exist: list each with repo, installed-at timestamp, skills/agents/hooks counts\n- Output totals: skill count, agent count, hook count, pack count\n\n### D. `search-marketplace`\n**Args:** `query` (required), `stack` (optional)\n**Flow:**\n- Call `SearchPacks(query)`\n- Filter by stack if provided (case-insensitive \"==\" or \"*\")\n- Output Markdown with matching packs\n\n### E. `onboard-project`\n**Args:** `project_name` (required), `description` (optional)\n**Flow:**\n- Detect stacks\n- Get recommended packs\n- Output step-by-step Markdown instructions:\n  1. Create project\n  2. Set stacks\n  3. Install recommended packs (with repo paths)\n  4. Verify (list packs, skills, agents)\n  5. Start working (create feature)\n\n**All prompts return:** `PromptGetResponse` with Description and Messages array (role=\"user\", content type=\"text\")\n\n---\n\n## 6. CLI PACK COMMANDS: `/libs/cli/internal/pack.go`\n\n**Subcommands:**\n```\norchestra pack install <repo>[@version]   # Clone, copy to .claude/, update registry\norchestra pack remove <name>              # Delete files, remove from registry\norchestra pack update [name]              # Rebuild from latest (if no name: all)\norchestra pack list                       # Display installed packs with counts\norchestra pack search <query>             # Search known packs\norchestra pack recommend                  # Detect stacks, show recommendations\n```\n\n**Registry Storage:**\n- Location: `.projects/.packs/registry.json`\n- Structure: `{ \"packs\": { \"pack-name\": {...} } }`\n- Entry fields: Version, Repo, InstalledAt (ISO8601), Stacks, Skills, Agents, Hooks\n\n**Key Functions:**\n- `installPackFromGit()` — Identical to plugin version; clones and copies files\n- `removePackFiles()` — Deletes skills, agents, hooks directories/files\n- `loadPackRegistry()` / `savePackRegistry()` — JSON persistence\n- Stack detection via: go.mod, Cargo.toml, package.json (react), tsconfig.json, etc.\n- Known packs: Same 17-pack hardcoded list (kept in sync with index.go)\n\n---\n\n## 7. SCRIPTS: `/scripts/install.sh`\n\n**Platform Installer Script:**\n- Detects OS (darwin/linux) and arch (amd64/arm64)\n- Downloads pre-built tarball from GitHub releases\n- Extracts to temp directory\n- Installs 5 binaries to `/usr/local/bin` (or `$INSTALL_DIR`):\n  - `orchestra`\n  - `orchestrator`\n  - `storage-markdown`\n  - `tools-features`\n  - `transport-stdio`\n- Sets executable permissions (0755)\n- Verifies with `orchestra version`\n\n**Usage:**\n```bash\ncurl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/orchestra-mcp/framework/master/scripts/install.sh | sh\n```\n\n**Env vars:** `INSTALL_DIR`, `VERSION`, `GITHUB_REPO`\n\n---\n\n## 8. HOMEBREW FORMULA: `/packaging/homebrew/orchestra.rb`\n\n**Formula Class:** `Orchestra < Formula`\n\n**Features:**\n- Detects macOS (arm64 / intel) and Linux (arm64 / intel)\n- Downloads matching platform tarball from GitHub releases\n- Installs 6 binaries to Homebrew bin directory:\n  - orchestra\n  - orchestrator\n  - storage-markdown\n  - tools-features\n  - transport-stdio\n  - tools-marketplace\n- Includes test: `assert_match version.to_s, shell_output(\"#{bin}/orchestra version\")`\n\n**Placeholders:**\n- `VERSION_PLACEHOLDER` — Version (must be replaced before release)\n- `SHA256_DARWIN_ARM64`, `SHA256_DARWIN_AMD64`, `SHA256_LINUX_ARM64`, `SHA256_LINUX_AMD64` — Checksums (must be computed)\n\n**Installation:**\n```bash\nbrew tap orchestra-mcp/tap\nbrew install orchestra\n# or\nbrew install orchestra-mcp/tap/orchestra\n```\n\n---\n\n## 9. NPM WRAPPER: `/packaging/npm/`\n\n**package.json:**\n- Name: `@orchestra-mcp/cli`\n- Version: `0.1.0`\n- Bin: `orchestra` → `./bin/orchestra`\n- Postinstall script: `node scripts/install.js`\n- Platforms: darwin, linux\n- CPUs: x64, arm64\n\n**install.js (Postinstall Script):**\n1. Maps platform/arch: darwin, linux; x64→amd64, arm64→arm64\n2. Constructs URL: `https://github.com/orchestra-mcp/framework/releases/download/v${VERSION}/orchestra-${platform}.tar.gz`\n3. Downloads tarball with HTTPS (follows redirects)\n4. Extracts to `./bin/`\n5. Makes 5 binaries executable (0755):\n   - orchestra\n   - orchestrator\n   - storage-markdown\n   - tools-features\n   - transport-stdio\n6. Cleans up tarball\n\n**Usage:**\n```bash\nnpm install @orchestra-mcp/cli\nnpx orchestra init\n```\n\n---\n\n## 10. STORAGE CLIENT: `/libs/plugin-tools-marketplace/internal/storage/client.go`\n\n**Key Structures:**\n- `StorageClient` interface — Single `Send()` method for plugin requests\n- `PackRegistry` — Root struct with Packs map\n- `PackEntry` — Version, Repo, InstalledAt, Stacks, Skills, Agents, Hooks\n- `PackStorage` — Wraps StorageClient, provides high-level read/write operations\n\n**Constants:**\n- `registryPath = \".packs/registry.json\"`\n- `stacksPath = \".packs/stacks.json\"`\n\n**Registry Operations:**\n- `ReadRegistry(ctx)` → Loads `.packs/registry.json`, parses to PackRegistry\n- `WriteRegistry(ctx, reg, expectedVersion)` → Persists PackRegistry with optimistic locking\n- `ReadStacks(ctx)` → Loads `.packs/stacks.json` as `{ \"stacks\": [...] }`\n- `WriteStacks(ctx, stacks, expectedVersion)` → Persists stacks array\n\n**Low-Level Protocol (Private):**\n- `storageRead()` — Sends PluginRequest with StorageReadRequest (path, storageType=\"markdown\")\n- `storageWrite()` — Sends PluginRequest with StorageWriteRequest (path, content, metadata, expectedVersion)\n- Uses protobuf StructPb to convert JSON metadata to/from structpb.Struct\n- Returns version for optimistic concurrency control\n\n---\n\n## 11. STACK DETECTION: `/libs/plugin-tools-marketplace/internal/packs/stacks.go`\n\n**StackInfo Struct:**\n- Name (e.g., \"go\", \"rust\")\n- Confidence (float64, always 1.0 in current impl)\n- Evidence (string describing what was found)\n\n**DetectStacks(workspace) → []StackInfo:**\n\nChecks for 12 stacks:\n1. **go** — `go.mod` or `go.work` exists\n2. **rust** — `Cargo.toml` exists\n3. **react** — `react` in package.json dependencies\n4. **typescript** — `tsconfig.json` exists\n5. **python** — `pyproject.toml`, `requirements.txt`, or `setup.py` exists\n6. **ruby** — `Gemfile` exists\n7. **java** — `pom.xml` or `build.gradle` exists\n8. **kotlin** — `build.gradle.kts` exists\n9. **swift** — `Package.swift` or `.xcodeproj` exists\n10. **csharp** — `.csproj` or `.sln` exists\n11. **php** — `composer.json` exists\n12. **docker** — `Dockerfile`, `docker-compose.yml`, or `docker-compose.yaml` exists\n\n**Special Checkers:**\n- `checkSwift()` — Glob for `.xcodeproj`\n- `checkCSharp()` — Glob for `.csproj` and `.sln`\n- `checkPackageJSONDep()` — Parses package.json, checks both dependencies and devDependencies\n\n---\n\n## 12. PLUGIN REGISTRATION: `/libs/plugin-tools-marketplace/internal/plugin.go`\n\n**MarketplacePlugin Struct:**\n- Storage: `*storage.PackStorage`\n- Workspace: `string`\n\n**RegisterTools(builder) → 15 Tools:**\n\n**Pack Management (6):**\n- `install_pack` — InstallPackSchema() + InstallPack(ps, ws)\n- `remove_pack` — RemovePackSchema() + RemovePack(ps, ws)\n- `update_pack` — UpdatePackSchema() + UpdatePack(ps, ws)\n- `list_packs` — ListPacksSchema() + ListPacks(ps)\n- `get_pack` — GetPackSchema() + GetPack(ps)\n- `search_packs` — SearchPacksSchema() + SearchPacks(ps)\n\n**Recommendations (2):**\n- `detect_stacks` — DetectStacksSchema() + DetectStacks(ws)\n- `recommend_packs` — RecommendPacksSchema() + RecommendPacks(ps, ws)\n\n**Content Queries (5):**\n- `list_skills` — ListSkillsSchema() + ListSkills(ws)\n- `list_agents` — ListAgentsSchema() + ListAgents(ws)\n- `list_hooks` — ListHooksSchema() + ListHooks(ws)\n- `get_skill` — GetSkillSchema() + GetSkill(ws)\n- `get_agent` — GetAgentSchema() + GetAgent(ws)\n\n**Configuration (2):**\n- `set_project_stacks` — SetProjectStacksSchema() + SetProjectStacks(ps)\n- `get_project_stacks` — GetProjectStacksSchema() + GetProjectStacks(ps, ws)\n\n**RegisterPrompts(builder) → 5 Prompts:**\nAll prompts listed in section 5 above\n\n---\n\n## ARCHITECTURE SUMMARY\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    Packs System Architecture                 │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n\n  CLI (orchestra pack <cmd>)  ←→  Plugin Tools (MCP prompts + tools)\n         ↓                                    ↓\n  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n  │           Pack Registry & Discovery                       │\n  │  index.go: 17 known packs + recommend/search logic        │\n  │  stacks.go: Auto-detect Go, Rust, React, TypeScript, etc │\n  │  prompts.go: 5 guided prompts for setup/audit/recommend   │\n  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n         ↓                                    ↓\n  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n  │            Pack Installation & Management                 │\n  │  installer.go: Git clone → copy to .claude/              │\n  │  pack.go: CLI commands (install/remove/update/list)      │\n  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n         ↓                                    ↓\n  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n  │           Storage & Persistence                           │\n  │  .projects/.packs/registry.json  (CLI)                    │\n  │  .packs/registry.json            (Plugin via Storage API)  │\n  │  .packs/stacks.json              (Configured stacks)      │\n  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n         ↓                                    ↓\n  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n  │           Workspace Content (.claude/)                    │\n  │  .claude/skills/<name>/SKILL.md   (Skill definitions)     │\n  │  .claude/agents/<name>.md         (Agent instructions)    │\n  │  .claude/hooks/<name>.sh          (Hook scripts)          │\n  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n\nRemote Repositories (GitHub):\n  /packs/pack-*/ (17 repos, each with pack.json + skills/ + agents/ + hooks/)\n  Installable via: orchestra pack install github.com/orchestra-mcp/pack-<name>[@version]\n```\n\n---\n\nAll files are absolute paths as requested. The packs system is a complete, self-contained subsystem for distributing and managing skills, agents, and hooks across projects."
